content: Edit: developer suggested trying the controller in a different mode, and I was able to get it working by setting it to Switch mode and UN-mapping d-pad inputs. Weird and a bit hacky, but okay. Bumping the review up as a result. --------- It seems to not work with the 8BitDo Lite bluetooth controller. When the controller is set to XInput mode and connected via bluetooth, VGBAnext thinks the controller is constantly holding the up button. If you turn on "Ignore Fake KeyUp Events", then it doesn't register up inputs at all. Lack of controller support is a pretty huge deal-breaker for me, and I've not had this issue with other emulators on Android (tested in Snes9x EX+ and PPSSPP). Until controller support is more robust, I'd steer clear unless you intend to only play with the touchscreen/virtual buttons.
replyContent: "Ignore fake KeyUp events" option won't help you, since it is used for certain buggy keyboards. I do not have an 8BitDo controller here, but have you tried setting it into modes other than XInput? Email me if you need help making your controller work.

replyContent: The problem with GBA GameLink protocol (use for NetPlay) is that both GameBoys keep exchanging too much data, WiFi just can't keep up. That is why it slows down so much. Of course, the REAL GameLink used a real, physical wire: no bandwidth problems there.
